    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Me</h2>
        <p>Hey there, my name is Charlie. I attended Towson University where I played baseball and ended up graduating with degrees in Sports Management and Business Administration.

           While I'm an East Coast guy to my core but I've lived in sunny SoCal with my wife for the last 4 years (rough life, I know). 

            I'm a huge dog lover and have 2 good boys. Oakley's a Golden Retriever-Hound mix (sounds like a seal) and Bodie is a red golden.
            I'm an avid sports fan and I'm passionate about sports analytics. Especially in the betting market.

             After graduating I began my career in the mortgage industry. I worked in sales, management, operations and underwriting. While living in California, I worked for a mortgage tech company
             called Better Mortgage. It was here where fell in love with technology and the user stories behind our product. I was fascinated with improving all aspects of the user journey and our 
             dynamic platform; UX/UI, user flows, data analysis, optimization and all of the other components that stand in front of a company and implementing a great B2C product.

            After leaving Better, I knew I wanted my next role to be within the product realm. With limited direct experience in product, I knew I needed to level up my skillset and knowledge
            so I listened to every product podcast I could find, read product books, took classes and started putting together my own projects. I learn best by doing.

            I was lucky enough to find a role at an early stage startup called Pingtree. It was here where I have been immersed in the product world. As well as, engineering, project management, data analysis, 
            SaaS sales, revenue ops and all of the roles one takes on at a small and scrappy startup.
        </p>
        </section>

